      "date": "2020-04-23 00:09:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhat happens if an old client (e.g. 2.12) tries to access an EC file?  Will it get an error because it doesn't understand the EC parity component, or could it try to select and read that component?  What happens if an old client tries to write to an EC file?  Will the MDS always mark the EC parity component stale?",
